                <head>No. 1404<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Telegram 438 to Baghdad, February 18, transmitted the text of the Mutual Defense
                    Assistance Program Agreement to be submitted to the Government of Iraq. Telegram
                    440, February 18, contained the Department of State’s comments on the text and
                    the legal reasons behind the writing of some sections. Telegram 441, February
                    18, instructed the Ambassador on the method of presentation of the agreement. He
                    was authorized to inform the Government of Iraq that the United States had
                    discussed the matter with the Government of the United Kingdom. The United
                    States considered its aid complementary to that of the United Kingdom, which
                    would continue to be the prime supplier of arms and training assistance to Iraq.
                    Documentation is in Department of State file 787.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1"
                        >MSP</gloss>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
